[ProMED-mail slipped up on this one. We received early notice of
the cases in army barracks, but chose not to post in the
expectation that the illness would remain confined there. We
should have known better.
Although this news report does not specify whether the meningitis
is bacterial (meningococcal) or viral, given the season of the year
& severity of the disease it is more likely the former, rather than the
ECHO-virus meningitis that afflicted Romania, & may have spread
to Hungary, in summer 1999 -- see: Meningitis, viral - Hungary ex
Romania? 19990819123712. - Mod.JW]
